			]
			title: "Less Rigorous Science"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["0B3C743441943C29"]
			description: [
				"Of course, as we all know, the primary goal of a scientist is not to gather results or data, but to gather &1citations&r. As many as possible."
				""
				"The good news is that once you get this process going, it's largely self-sustaining. Sure, your first &9scientific paper&r required a large amount of research and data, but now you can just feed it back into the &9Sciencery&r endlessly for more papers and more citations."
				""
				"Really, the hardest part will be keeping up a supply of &9paper&r to publish all this on. Build yourself a &9sugar cane&r farm and teach a rat how to craft that into &9paper&r."
			]
			id: "41F5F15BE95C79DC"
			tasks: [{
				id: "308B395091D61DFE"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "kubejs:citations_bucket"
					tag: { }
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Citations"
			x: 3.5d
			y: 2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["6079EDB456F3DE89"]
			description: ["It's finally time to publish! Just pour your results all over some &9paper&r, I'm sure the journals will love the first draft."]
			id: "01B494C61A52BB02"
			subtitle: "Or perish, whichever"
			tasks: [{
